<HEADLINE>
AIKMAN RETURNS, MIGHT FACE REDSKINS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Troy Aikman and Randall Cunningham split time at
quarterback in the Cowboys' practice Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   After the workout Aikman said he felt fine and that he did not
experience any recurrence of the symptoms stemming from the
concussion against the Philadelphia Eagles that kept him out of
last week's game against the Arizona Cardinals.
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys coach Dave Campo, however, will wait at least until
after Aikman goes through practice today before making a final
decision on who will start against the Washington Redskins on
Monday night. Aikman will start if he is healthy, and Cunningham
will return to his duties as backup quarterback. ``Troy looked
good,'' Campo said. ``We are fortunate to have an extra day. It
will give us more evaluation time. I'd like to have everything done
by Thursday. But I honestly don't have a timetable.''
</P>
<P>
   Aikman said he will talk in more detail about his status today.
</P>
<P>
   Aikman's presence was welcomedby teammates, and his efforts in
practice passed their eye test, especially tight end Jackie
Harris'.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was good to see him back out there, moving around and
throwing the ball, screaming at guys, that kind of thing,'' said a
laughing Harris, who added a ``Nah'' to the last part.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't expect him not to play,'' Harris said.
</P>
<P>
   Added tight end David LaFleur: ``Troy's Troy. He came out there
and threw the ball around and looked like his old self. I guess he
felt good. If it's left up to Troy, I think he's definitely going
to be out there \Ragainst the Redskins\S.'' \Nsubheds:No interest
in Smith A source said the Cowboys have no interest in re-signing
cornerback Kevin Smith, despite their struggles at the position.
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys vice president Stephen Jones, who declined to discuss
Smith's future, said the team simply abided by Smith's wishes when
they removed him from the reserve-retired list and released him
Tuesday. \Nsubheds:Stupid question? Unnamed reporter: Will a win
over the Redskins erase what happened in the first two games?
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys center Mark Stepnoski: ``We'll still be 1-2. There's no
erasing what happened in the first two weeks, because that's done.
It's on the record regardless.''
</P>
<P>
   \Nsubheds:Briefly Right guard Solomon Page missed practice
Wednesday because of a strained hamstring. He is listed as
questionable for Monday's game against Washington. If he can't
play, Jorge Diaz will start. Running back Chris Warren (strained
neck) is also listed as questionable.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys signed rookie free-agent defensive tackle Ron Moore
to the practice squad. Moore was drafted by the Green Bay Packers
in the seventh round of the 2000 draft out of Northwestern
Oklahoma. He was cut in training camp. nn
</P>
</TEXT>
