<HEADLINE>
SECOND WINSTON CUP DATE REMAINS ELUSIVE FOR TEXAS SPEEDWAY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By LEN HAYWARD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ The 2001 schedule at Texas Motor Speedway
will feature all three of NASCAR's top series, both American
open-wheel series, the nation's top dirt-track series and a
road-racing series.
</P>
<P>
   In all, the track that now officially bills itself as ``The
Great American Speedway'' will host five major weekends _ two in
March and one each in April, June and September.
</P>
<P>
   But missing again from a jam-packed schedule announced yesterday
by Eddie Gossage, TMS' executive vice president and general
manager, was the coveted second Winston Cup and stand-alone Busch
Grand National races. Even though both schedules have not been
released by NASCAR, it's well known that TMS will not have a second
Winston Cup date next year. But Gossage has not lost hope on a
second Busch race in 2001.
</P>
<P>
   Gossage said he requested a second Busch race, mainly because
the series will not compete at South Boston, Va., and Myrtle Beach,
S.C.. He has yet to hear anything from NASCAR regarding the
request.
</P>
<P>
   Gossage said he talked to Mike Helton, NASCAR's senior vice
president and chief operating officer recently, but Helton didn't
reveal much.
</P>
<P>
   ``If they say yes we're going to take it and we'll find a place
for it,'' Gossage said. ``I have no news on the second Winston Cup
race. This is a unique year because the TV deal has changed and
\RNASCAR\S is trying to sort it all out. They are not quite ready
to announce the schedule. \RHelton\S didn't say no and he didn't
say yes \Rto the Busch race\S.''
</P>
<P>
   Even with those two omissions, the track will host two events
for the Indy Racing Northern Light Series, its inaugural race in
the Championship Auto Racing Teams FedEx Series and the American Le
Mans Series.
</P>
<P>
   The marquee event remains the April 1 DirecTV 500 NASCAR Winston
Cup race.
</P>
<P>
   The Cup week is billed as ``RPM Week _ Texas,'' and features
five days of racing, with events at the 1.5-mile superspeedway and
the four-tenths mile dirt track. The TMS Dirt Track will play host
to a Hav-A-Tampa Series race on March 28 and a two-day Pennzoil
World of Outlaws event March 29-30.
</P>
<P>
   A similar ``RPM Week _ Texas'' is scheduled Sept. 13-16. Along
with the season finale for the Indy Racing Northern Light Series,
the NASCAR Craftsman Truck Series will run on Sept. 15. At the dirt
track, the Hav-A-Tampa Series will run the Wolf Brand Chili 100 on
Sept. 13. A two-day Outlaws program is set for Sept. 14-15.
</P>
<P>
   The schedule opens March 1-4 with the second ALMS Grand Prix of
Texas on the combined oval/infield road course. Gossage added
Monster Truck, Freestyle Motocross and dirt-track motorcycle events
to the schedule at the TMS Dirt Track.
</P>
<P>
   ``We may be pushing the envelope and we will find out what the
market will bear,'' Gossage said. ``But it's like Rick Mears once
told me, `Until you spin the car out you don't know where your
limit is.' We haven't spun out yet. Maybe we are in 2001 and,
again, we'll find out.''
</P>
<P>
   \Nsubheds:TMS 2001 Schedule Superspeedway and Road Course
</P>
<P>
   March 1-4: Grand Prix of Texas, American Le Mans Series
</P>
<P>
   March 31: Texas 300, NASCAR Busch Series
</P>
<P>
   April 1: DirecTV 500, NASCAR Winston Cup
</P>
<P>
   April 29: Texas 600, CART FedEx Championship Series
</P>
<P>
   June 8: Fort Worth 400, NASCAR Craftsman Truck Series
</P>
<P>
   June 9: Casino Magic 500, Indy Racing Northern Light Series
</P>
<P>
   Sept. 15: O'Reilly 400, NASCAR Craftsman Truck Series
</P>
<P>
   Sept. 16: Lone Star 500, Indy Racing Northern Light Series
</P>
<P>
   DIRT TRACK
</P>
<P>
   March 28: Hav-A-Tampa Dirt Late Models, TMS Dirt Track
</P>
<P>
   March 29-30: Southern Bleacher Classic, Pennzoil World of
Outlaws, TMS Dirt Track
</P>
<P>
   Sept. 13: Wolf Brand Chili 100, Hav-A-Tampa Dirt Late Models,
TMS Dirt Track
</P>
<P>
   Sept. 14-15: O'Reilly Texas Showdown, Pennzoil World of Outlaws,
TMS Dirt Track
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
