<HEADLINE>
NFL CAPSULES FOR WEEK 3
</HEADLINE>
 CAPSULES-TEX (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By STEPHEN SCHROATS 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
BUFFALO BILLS AT NEW YORK JETS WHEN: Noon, Sunday RECORDS: Bills
2-0, Jets 2-0 SERIES: Bills lead, 44-34 LAST REGULAR-SEASON
MEETING: Jets won, 17-7, on Nov. 21, 1999, as their defense forces
three turnovers and scores once. THE LINE: Jets by 1 1/2 THE SCOOP
_ The Bills are 2-0 for the first time since 1996. Both wins have
come at home. _ In his past six starts, Bills QB Rob Johnson is 6-0
with 10 TDs and one interception. _ The Jets have not started a
season 3-0 since 1966. _ Jets QB Vinny Testaverde has been the best
fourth-quarter quarterback in the NFL the first two weeks,
completing 14 of 19 passes for 270 yards and three touchdowns. _
Jets WR Dedric Ward has back-to-back 100-yard receiving games. The
last Jet receiver with three in a row was Al Toon in 1988. THE
PICK: Bills' first ``road game'' not a bad trip. Bills 27-20
ATLANTA FALCONS AT CAROLINA PANTHERS WHEN: Noon, Sunday RECORDS:
Falcons 1-1, Panthers 1-1 SERIES: Tied, 5-5 LAST REGULAR-SEASON
MEETING: Panthers won, 34-28, on Nov. 28, 1999, as Steve Beuerlein
throws three TD passes. THE LINE: Panthers by 6 THE SCOOP _ In the
10-game series, the Falcons have outscored the Panthers, 209-208. _
The Falcons gained only 44 yards in the first half against the
Broncos, and trailed 27-0 before getting their initial first down
with 8:10 left in the half. _ Falcons WR Shawn Jefferson averages
20.6 yards per catch, second in NFC. _ Panthers QB Steve Beuerlein
has completed 71 percent of his passes (41 of 58), second-best in
the NFL. _ Panthers WR Muhsin Muhammad has 14 catches for 156 yards
but his status is uncertain for this game. _ Panthers TE Wesley
Walls leads NFL with 14 TD receptions since the start of 1999
season. THE PICK: Too close to call, so stay with home team.
Panthers, 31-30.
SAN FRANCISCO 49ERS AT ST. LOUIS RAMS WHEN: Noon, Sunday RECORDS:
49ers 0-2, Rams 2-0 SERIES: Rams lead, 50-48-2 LAST REGULAR-SEASON
MEETING: Rams won, 23-7, on Nov. 21, 1999, as defense forces five
Niners turnovers. THE LINE: Rams by 16 1/2 THE SCOOP _ Until being
swept last season, the 49ers had won all but one game between these
teams in the 1990s. _ The 49ers, who had won seven straight home
openers, lost 38-22 to Carolina, the 49ers' worst loss in a home
opener since 1988. _ 49ers FB Fred Beasley leads NFC with four TDs
(two rushing, two receiving). _ The Rams set an NFL record by
scoring 30 or more points in their eighth consecutive
regular-season game. _ In St. Louis' two games, QB Kurt Warner is
60-for-80 for 827 yards passing and four touchdowns, with four
interceptions _ two returned for touchdowns. Warner's 827 yards
passing is an NFL record for a season's first two games. _ Rams RB
Marshall Faulk has 331 total yards; 146 rushing and 13 receptions
for 185 yards. THE PICK: Payback is a ... Rams, 46-13
PHILADELPHIA EAGLES AT GREEN BAY PACKERS WHEN: Noon, Sunday
RECORDS: Eagles 1-1, Packers 0-2 SERIES: Packers lead, 21-9 LAST
REGULAR-SEASON MEETING: Packers won, 24-16, on Nov. 29, 1998, as
Darick Holmes rushes for career-high 163 yards. THE LINE: Packers
by 4 THE SCOOP _ Eagles RB Duce Staley, who ran for 201 yards
against Dallas, had 11 yards on seven carries against the Giants.
He shares NFC lead with 331 total yards. _ The Eagles, who led the
NFL with 46 takeaways last season, didn't get any against the
Giants. _ The Packers gained only 40 yards rushing against Buffalo.
_ Packers Brett Favre, who extended his NFL record with his 127th
consecutive start at QB, completed his first 14 passes before
ending 25-of-35 for 269 yards. _ The Packers start 0-2 for the
first time in eight seasons. _ Packers WR Antonio had seven catches
for 80 yards _ all in the second half. THE PICK: Are the Eagles
that good? The Packers that bad? No, and no. Packers, 24-20.
TAMPA BAY BUCCANEERS AT DETROIT LIONS WHEN: Noon, Sunday RECORDS:
Buccaneers 2-0, Lions 2-0 SERIES: Lions lead, 25-19 LAST
REGULAR-SEASON MEETING: Buccaneers won, 23-16, on Dec. 12, 1999, as
Shaun King throws a 22-yard TD pass to Mike Alstott with 4:18 left.
THE LINE: Buccaneers by 3 THE SCOOP _ Its 41-0 rout of Chicago was
Tampa Bay's largest margin of victory in history. _ The Buccaneers
have not allowed a Bears touchdown in 14 quarters, and only allowed
nine total points in their past three meetings. _ The Bucs scored
on five of their last seven possessions against the Bears. _ Under
coach Tony Dungy, the Bucs are 26-2 in games they lead after three
quarters. _ The Lions are 2-0 and have yet to score an offensive
TD. They scored on a kickoff return and interception to win in New
Orleans and got five Jason Hanson field goals to beat the Redskins.
_ The Lions have won six of the past seven home games against the
Bucs. THE PICK: Two things that haven't happened this season: a
Lions offensive TD and a Bucs loss. Lions, 19-17
CINCINNATI BENGALS AT JACKSONVILLE JAGUARS WHEN: Noon, Sunday
RECORDS: Bengals 0-1, Jaguars 1-1 SERIES: Jaguars lead, 6-4 LAST
REGULAR-SEASON MEETING: Jaguars won, 24-7, on Jan. 2, 2000, as
Jimmy Smith caught 14 passes for 165 yards. THE LINE: Jaguars by 13
THE SCOOP _ The Bengals are 7-29 in August and September the past
10 years. _ Against the Browns, the Bengals fumbled three times,
had a field-goal attempt blocked and allowed seven sacks. _ Bengals
rookie WR Peter Warrick, who had brashly predicted a victory
against the Browns, dropped three passes along with his three
catches. _ Jaguars receiver Jimmy Smith caught 15 passes for 291
yards and three TDs vs. Baltimore. It was the fifth-highest
receiving yardage mark in league history and most since Rams WR
Willie Anderson set the NFL record with 336 on Nov. 26, 1989. _ In
blowing a 23-7 lead to the Ravens, the Jaguars lost for the first
time in two seasons to a team other than the Titans. _ The Jaguars
have won 29 of their past 33 home games, including playoffs, and 16
of their past 21 AFC Central games. THE PICK: No doubt who is the
top cat. Jaguars, 37-14.
PITTSBURGH STEELERS AT CLEVELAND BROWNS WHEN: Noon, Sunday RECORDS:
Steelers 0-1, Browns 1-1 SERIES: Browns lead, 53-41 LAST
REGULAR-SEASON MEETING: Browns won, 16-15, as Phil Dawson kicks a
39-yard field goal as time expires. THE LINE: Steelers by 2 1/2 THE
SCOOP _ After a week off, the Steelers now play seven of next eight
against AFC Central rivals. _ Steelers RB Jerome Bettis gained 8
yards on nine carries in Week 1, his lowest rushing output in five
seasons. _ In his first NFL game, WR Plaxico Burress caught four
passes for 77 yards, each for a first down. _ Browns P Chris
Gardocki set an NFL record, extending his streak of punts without a
block to 630. _ Browns RB Travis Prentice, a rookie from nearby
Miami (Ohio), scored the first official touchdown in Paul Brown
Stadium on a 16-yard run. _ The Browns' 354 yards against the
Bengals was Cleveland's most in 18 games as an expansion team. _
Browns QB Tim Couch completed passes to 10 receivers last week. THE
PICK: Expansion Browns' first win streak. Browns, 24-19.
DENVER BRONCOS AT OAKLAND RAIDERS WHEN: 3:05 p.m., Sunday RECORDS:
Broncos 1-1, Raiders 2-0 SERIES: Raiders lead, 49-28-2 LAST
REGULAR-SEASON MEETING: Broncos won, 27-21 in OT, on Nov. 22, 1999,
as Jason Elam kicks three field goals. THE LINE: Raiders by 3 THE
SCOOP _ Broncos RB Mike Anderson, a 27-year-old ex-Marine, stepped
in for injured backs Terrell Davis and Olandis Gary and ran for 131
yards against Atlanta. He is the first Broncos rookie to rush for
100 yards in his first start. _ The Broncos scored on their first
five possessions en route to a 34-7 halftime lead against the
Falcons. _ Broncos QB Brian Griese has five TD passes, no
interceptions. _ The Raiders are seeking their first 3-0 start
since 1990. _ The Raiders had five rushing TDs at Indianapolis,
including a career-high three by QB Rich Gannon, who had only 12
rushing TDs in his first 13 years. _ The Raiders won on the road
despite a 21-point deficit to the Colts. _ The Raiders' victories
have been by 9-6 and 38-31. THE PICK: Raiders perform better as
underdogs. Broncos, 27-21.
SAN DIEGO CHARGERS AT KANSAS CITY CHIEFS WHEN: 3:05 p.m., Sunday
RECORDS: Chargers 0-2, Chiefs 0-2 SERIES: Chiefs lead, 41-36-1 LAST
REGULAR-SEASON MEETING: Chiefs won, 34-0, on Oct. 31, 1999, as
defense gets five sacks and forces four turnovers. THE LINE: Chiefs
by 5 THE SCOOP _ Chargers QB Ryan Leaf threw his first touchdown
pass since Oct. 25, 1998, a 20-yarder to Curtis Conway, in the
Chargers' loss to the Saints. _ Leaf has one TD pass and five
interceptions this season. _ John Carney kicked two field goals and
three PATs to reach 1,004 career points, making him the first
Chargers player to surpass the 1,000-point milestone. _ Chiefs QB
Elvis Grbac has two TD passes in each of three starts against the
Chargers. THE PICK: Are the Chiefs that bad? No, but the Chargers
are. Chiefs, 27-10
NEW YORK GIANTS AT CHICAGO BEARS WHEN: 3:15 p.m., Sunday RECORDS:
Giants 2-0, Bears 0-2 SERIES: Bears lead, 25-16-2 LAST
REGULAR-SEASON MEETING: Bears won, 27-24, on Nov. 26, 1995, as
Kevin Butler kicks a 37-yard field goal with seven seconds left.
THE LINE: Bears by 2 1/2  nflsmhed:THE SCOOP  nflbody:_ The Giants
are 2-0 for the first time in six years. _ Giants QB Kerry Collins
has been sacked once for no yards in two games. _ Giants RB Tiki
Barber has slashed for 240 yards in 24 carries in two games. Last
season, the Giants' leading rusher had 348 yards all season. _
Giants coach Jim Fassel improved to 7-0 lifetime against the
Eagles. _ The Bears' 41-0 loss at Tampa Bay was their first shutout
since Dec. 24, 1989 _ a stretch of 161 regular-season and five
playoff games _ when they lost 26-0 to San Francisco. _ Bears QB
Cade McNown has led team in rushing in first two games. _ Bears WR
Marcus Robinson has caught seven TD passes from McNown, averaging
41.3 yards per score. THE PICK: Giants find out nobody wins them
all. Bears 24-21.
NEW ORLEANS SAINTS AT SEATTLE SEAHAWKS WHEN: 3:15 p.m., Sunday
RECORDS: Saints 1-1, Seahawks 0-2 SERIES: Saints lead, 4-2 LAST
REGULAR-SEASON MEETING: Saints won, 20-17 in OT, on Nov. 16, 1997,
as Winfred Tubbs intercepts a pass on the first play of OT, setting
up winning field goal. THE LINE: Seahawks by 6 THE SCOOP _ The
Saints snapped a 14-game road losing streak at San Diego. It was
their first road victory since beating Indianapolis, 19-13, in
overtime on Sept. 27, 1998. _ Saints WR Joe Horn caught 12 passes
for a career-high 116 yards. He leads the NFC with 17 receptions. _
Seahawks RB Ricky Watters leads the team in rushing (118 yards),
receiving (8-76) and scoring (2 TDs). THE PICK: Saints have met
their road quota. Seahawks, 28-20.
MINNESOTA VIKINGS AT NEW ENGLAND PATRIOTS WHEN: 3:15 p.m., Sunday
RECORDS: Vikings 2-0, Patriots 0-2 SERIES: Patriots lead, 4-3 LAST
REGULAR-SEASON MEETING: Vikings won, 23-18, on Nov. 2, 1997, as
Cris Carter has eight catches for 116 yards and a TD. THE LINE:
Patriots by 1 THE SCOOP _ The past three meetings have been decided
by six points or less. _ Vikings PK Gary Anderson needs 36 points
to pass George Blanda (2,002) as the NFL's all-time leading scorer.
_ The Patriots rank third in the AFC with a 33:13 average time of
possession (behind Denver, Jacksonville). _ Patriots' Kevin Faulk
leads NFL RBs with 15 catches and is tied for the NFL-high with six
third-down catches. _ The Patriots got inside the Jets' 20 five
times in the first half Monday and came away with only four field
goals. THE PICK: Some day Culpepper will play like a rookie. Not
today. Vikings, 27-17
BALTIMORE RAVENS AT MIAMI DOLPHINS WHEN: 7:35 p.m., Sunday RECORDS:
Ravens 2-0, Dolphins 1-1 SERIES: Dolphins lead, 1-0 LAST
REGULAR-SEASON MEETING: Dolphins won, 24-13, on Oct. 19, 1997, as
Karim Abdul-Jabbar rushes for 108 yards and three first-half TDs.
THE LINE: Ravens by 2 1/2 THE SCOOP _ The Ravens are seeking their
first 3-0 start ever. Since 1990, seven AFC Central teams have
started 3-0; six of them made the playoffs. _ Ravens QB Tony Banks
has six TD passes in first two games. He totaled 17 TDs in 10
starts last season. _ The Ravens' run defense leads the NFL by
allowing only 38 yards per game and 1.9 yards per carry. _ Ravens
PK Matt Stover has made 22 consecutive field goals, the longest
active streak in the NFL. _ The Dolphins have not lost at home in
September since 1993, 11 consecutive wins. _ Dolphins WR Tony
Martin leads the team with eight catches and 139 yards, but is
questionable for Sunday's game. THE PICK: Two good ``D''s. But only
one ``O.'' Ravens, 26-15.
DALLAS COWBOYS AT WASHINGTON REDSKINS WHEN: 8 p.m., Monday RECORDS:
Cowboys 0-2, Redskins 1-1 SERIES: Cowboys lead, 45-31-2 LAST
REGULAR-SEASON MEETING: Cowboys won, 41-35 in OT, on Oct. 24, 1999,
as Troy Aikman throws for two TDs and runs for another. THE LINE:
Redskins by 10 1/2 THE SCOOP _ These teams combined for 134 points
and 1,669 total yards in two games last season. _ The Cowboys have
won five in a row against the Redskins. _ Cowboys RB Emmitt Smith
rushed for 59 yards against the Cardinals to become the third
player in NFL history to rush for 14,000 yards. _ Cowboys QB
Randall Cunningham completed his first 13 pass attempts against the
Cardinals. That, and his completion on his last attempt in the
opener, tied the Cowboys record of 14 straight completions, set by
Steve Pelluer against Seattle on Nov. 27, 1986. Cunningham ended
Sunday night's game with four consecutive incompletions. _ The
Cardinals' 32 points against Dallas were their most against the
Cowboys since a 38-0 victory in 1970. _ Redskins QB Brad Johnson
threw a career-high four interceptions against the Lions. THE PICK:
The Cowboys always seem to beat the Redskins. Not this time.
Redskins, 37-23. OPEN: Indianapolis, Arizona, Tennessee nn
