<P>
   ATTENTION ALL EDITORS:
</P>
<P>
   This year's Olympics are a showcase of science as well as skill.
Witness:
</P>
<P>
   _ A Teflon-coated, formfitting bodysuit that helps swimmers
glide through water with greater efficiency.
</P>
<P>
   _ A punching bag embedded with an accelerometer, a three-inch
wafer of circuitry that translates the pounding of a jab into
schematics displayed on a computer screen.
</P>
<P>
   _ The new SuperBike III, a machine that has an aerodynamic frame
and silk tires pumped to 250 pounds pressure per square inch.
</P>
<P>
   To help your readers learn more about the new technology that is
changing the Games, The New York Times Syndicate has transmitted an
article titled ``THE USA's HIGH-TECH EDGE AT THE OLYMPICS,'' from
Discover magazine. It is available as a ``separate-buy.''
</P>
