   PIERRE-GILLES-PHOTOS (New York) _ The New Museum of Contemporary
Art in SoHo presents a long overdue introduction in the United
States of the French photo team known as Pierre et Gilles. It is a
must-see for anyone interested in the intertwining histories of
postmodern (especially set-up) photography, fashion photography,
commercial illustration, the male nude in art and the emergence of
a gay sensibility. By Roberta Smith.
