are a few other things about ``Crime and Punishment in Suburbia,''
directed by Rob Schmidt, that might lead you to believe it has
something to do with Dostoyevsky. Reviewed by A.O. Scott.
</P>
<P>
   GOYA-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ Carlos Saura's visual knockout of a
film, ``Goya in Bordeaux,'' forcefully conjures up the spirit of
Goya, who died in exile in Bordeaux (France), portraying him as an
unstoppable bull of a man and an artistic visionary whose greatest
work fearlessly locked horns with the darkest human truths.
Reviewed by Lawrence Van Gelder.
</P>
<P>
   ARMS-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Into the Arms of Strangers,'' a
new documentary by Mark Jonathan Harris, tells the story of a group
of Jewish children from Germany, Austria and Czechoslovakia who
were fortunate enough to escape, thanks to the Kindertransport,
which took 10,000 children to the safety of England in the late
1930s. Reviewed by A.O. Scott.
</P>
