<P>
   BRITAIN-FUEL (London) _ A blockade of British refineries and
storage areas began to break up Thursday, and convoys of oil trucks
moved past company gates unimpeded for the first time in a week.
But Prime Minister Tony Blair warned there was still ``some way to
go'' before drivers would see gasoline back in their neighborhood
pumps. By Warren Hoge.
