   EURO-RATES (Frankfurt) _ Faced with a sliding euro, the European
Central Bank said Thursday that it will buy 2.5 billion euros over
the next few days and sell mostly dollars and some Japanese yen.
The central bank left interest rates unchanged, as expected. By
Edmund L. Andrews.
</P>
