   LONDON-EXCHANGE (London) _ The chief executive of the London
Stock Exchange, Gavin Casey, barely retained his post in a secret
ballot taken after the demise of the exchange's planned merger with
the Frankfurt exchange. By Alan Cowell and Suzanne Kapner.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-WEB (Shanghai) _ Internet portal Sohu.com has announced
plans to take over rival ChinaRen.com in a deal to create China's
largest Web company, possibly heralding a wave of consolidation. By
Craig S. Smith.
</P>
<P>
   PHILIPPINES-ECON (Singapore) _ A potent combination of regional
political instability, rising debts and other signs of economic
weakness has rocked financial markets in the Philippines, sending
the currency to its lowest level since the Asian economic crisis
three years ago. By Wayne Arnold.
