pulling in the reins lately, too. By Sana Siwolop.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-INSIGHT-Q&AMP;A (Undated) _ With the group of stocks that is
leading the stock market higher getting larger, Marshall Acuff,
equity strategist at Salomon Smith Barney, thinks that there are
new opportunities for investors. The broadening process in the
market has accelerated as investors have become convinced that the
Federal Reserve has managed to slow the rapid pace of economic
growth and, therefore, will not have to raise short-term interests
again anytime soon. And this, in turn, has encouraged an increasing
number of stocks to rally. By Jonathan Fuerbringer.
