   ISRAEL-BARAK (Jerusalem) _ Yehud Barak talks about breaking
Israel's governmental logjam by trying to short-circuit the power
of small Orthodox religious parties. Skeptics see his speech on
secularizing Israel as populist rhetoric for short-term political
gain. By Charles M. Sennott. 800 words.
</P>
