   BRITAIN-ANALYSIS (London) _ The Blair government has been caught
in a rare misread of public opinion, as many British _ looking
enviously at lower-priced gasoline in Ireland and France _ wonder
by their budget-surplus, oil-producing nation needs to keep the
fuel tax pumped up. By Kevin Cullen. 750 words.
</P>
