   DEBATE-FORMAT (Washington) _ According to research by the
Commission on Presidential Debates, people don't care if the
candidates are sitting or standing. Or whether the debate's on
Larry King or at a university. What they want is as few journalists
as possible and about 20 minutes per topic. By Mary Leonard. 900
words.
</P>
