   LEE-RELEASE-CLINTON (Washington) _ President Clinton said
Thursday that he was ``quite troubled'' by the government's conduct
in the Wen Ho Lee case one day after a U.S. district court judge in
New Mexico harshly criticized federal authorities for unfair and
abusive tactics. The government's abandonment of the case that it
had once compared to nuclear espionage shattered an uneasy calm
that had settled over the Justice Department and the FBI in the
waning months of the Clinton presidency. By David Johnston.
