<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the stories New York Times editors are planning for
Page 1, Friday, Sept. 15. The night supervisor for The New York
Times News Service is Pat Ryan; phone: 888-346-9867 or
212-556-1927; e-mail: patryan(at)nytimes.com.
</P>
<P>
   TOP
</P>
<P>
   Lead story:
</P>
<P>
   LEE-RELEASE-CLINTON (Washington) _ President Clinton says he is
``quite troubled'' by the government's actions in the Wen Ho Lee
case, commenting one day after a federal judge in New Mexico
harshly criticized the Justice Department for tactics the judge
said were unfair and abusive. By David Johnston. (Eds.: an early
version of this story has moved; the 1stLd-Writethru is scheduled
to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.) 1,400 words.
</P>
<P>
   (EDS: budgeted earlier as LEE-RELEASE-RENO)
</P>
<P>
   With photos of President Clinton and Janet Reno.
</P>
