calls to get him there to begin with. Mad as hell and not going to
take it any more? Let it out with the help of enastyletter.com. Its
mission: to help people who ``fall victim to shoddy service but
don't have the time or inclination to complain.'' Take a few
minutes this weekend to send them the basics and, for $25 (a
one-pager with minimum research), they'll turn it into a letter of
impact, perhaps one that will extract a little coinage for your
wasted time. They even offer to scribe a Dear John letter.
