<P>
   FINDING TREASURE IN YOUR TRASH
</P>
<P>
   Those pesky plastic milk jugs and worn-out dryer sheets must be
good for something. In case you didn't realize, you can recycle
most of those common items you hate to throw away. Learn the
multiple uses of dishwashing liquid (works in a pinch as shower
gel) and vapor rub (makes a fine insect repellent).
</P>
<P>
   www.homestead.com/20uses
</P>
<P>
   DON'T GET MAD, GET EVEN: TELL 'EM WHERE TO GET OFF!
</P>
<P>
   So the cable installer due last Saturday didn't arrive until
last night _ and then two hours later than planned. It took five
calls to get him there to begin with. Mad as hell and not going to
take it any more? Let it out with the help of enastyletter.com. Its
mission: to help people who ``fall victim to shoddy service but
don't have the time or inclination to complain.'' Take a few
minutes this weekend to send them the basics and, for $25 (a
one-pager with minimum research), they'll turn it into a letter of
impact, perhaps one that will extract a little coinage for your
wasted time. They even offer to scribe a Dear John letter.
</P>
<P>
   www.enastyletter.com
</P>
<P>
   SITE LETS YOU SHARE YOUR PASSIONS WITH OTHERS
</P>
<P>
   Ah, the weekend. Time for a little gardening? Perhaps exploring
another sort of roots, as in family trees? Perhaps even the latest
from the political front? Whatever your interest, hobby or chore,
visit Themestream, ``the Web's leading enthusiast resource.'' Just
sign up for your favorite topics and you can read articles about
them from other enthusiasts. You can even get new articles via
e-mail. Coming soon: Discussion and message boards to chat with
others with your interests.
</P>
<P>
   www.themestream.com
</P>
