<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR FRIDAY, SEPT. 15 
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: These corrections appeared in The New York Times on Friday,
Sept. 15. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.) 
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-COMPUTER-BRIEFS-NYT (moved Sunday, September 10)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, September
10 about the settlement of a dispute over some types of digital
television sets made by Hitachi and Toshiba referred incorrectly to
the adjoining picture. It showed a standard high-definition TV,
which has a wide screen _ not the type covered by &QC; the settlement.
The companies gained the right to use the high-definition label for
sets that have nearly square screens, so long as they notify buyers
that the picture will have a lower resolution than that of a
standard high-definition set.
</P>
<P>
   BC-INKTOMI-FASTFORWARD-NYT (moved Wednesday, September 13)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday,
September 13 about the Inktomi Corp.'s deal to acquire FastForward
Networks misstated Inktomi's base. It is Foster City, Calif., not
Forest City.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-WHYTE-NYT (moved Tuesday, September 12)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service obituary sent on Tuesday,
September 12 about Donald Whyte, a violinist in the New York
Philharmonic, misstated his age. He was 58, not 68.
</P>
