<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-14 22:25 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5889 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r f BC-VIRGIN-QUICK-LADN     09-14 0413
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VIRGIN-QUICK-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MADONNA AT YOUR FRONT DOOR IN 30 MINUTES?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JESSE HIESTAND 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   CAMARILLO, Calif. _ Need your ``Music'' fast?
</P>
<P>
   A few retailers will stay open past midnight Monday to sell the
eagerly anticipated Madonna release the minute it is available to
the public. Similar sales of big-name albums have drawn crowds and
long lines.
</P>
<P>
   Now, fans more likely to be in their pajamas at that time don't
have to miss out.
</P>
<P>
   Camarillo-based home delivery firm PDQuick plans to test a new
service in the Los Angeles region _ delivering the disc to your
doorstep in about 30 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   ``Time is of the essence with her fans, so this fits into what
we do for our customers,'' said Dan Frederickson, president and
chief executive officer of PDQuick, a direct-to-home retailer of
food, groceries and other products. ``If customers show us they
like it, we'd like to carry other new releases.''
</P>
<P>
   The venture, called ``Skip the Trip,'' is a partnership of
PDQuick and two arms of the Virgin media empire, Virginmega.com and
Virgin Megastores, where people can buy Madonna's album beginning
at 12:01 a.m. Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ``This release is probably the biggest CD to come out in the
last three months and really signals the beginning of the Christmas
market,'' said Dave Alder, general manager and senior vice
president of Virgin Megastore Online.
</P>
<P>
   Other big releases may be delivered this way if the experiment
goes well, the companies said.
</P>
<P>
   ``The customer will tell us at the end of the day whether or not
it's a service they find useful,'' Alder said.
</P>
<P>
   Virgin is supplying the CD to PDQuick for sale either through
the delivery company's toll-free number or Web site
(www.pdquick.com).
</P>
<P>
   It will be available in PDQuick's service area in Orange and Los
Angeles counties, including the San Fernando Valley.
</P>
<P>
   Customers will be charged the standard $2.99 delivery fee
applied to orders of any size, Frederickson said. There is no
minimum order, and the service stays open through 3 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   The price for the CD has not yet been determined but
Frederickson said it would be competitive with other retailers.
</P>
<P>
   Frederickson said he does not expect a flood of orders to tax or
overload the company's fleet of delivery vehicles.
</P>
<P>
   PDQuick most recently started operating in San Diego and next
plans to launch in the Washington, D.C, and Baltimore areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
