<P>
   (NYT37) COLON, Cuba -- Sept. 14, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN. SEPT. 17
-- CUBA-MIGRATION-COX-1 -- Daisy Bueno, 41, of Colon, Cuba with
Chester, a boxer that belonged to her two dead sons, Juan Carlos,
23, and Alexei, 20. The two were killed in early August by sharks
as they attempted to cross the Florida Straits from Cuba to the
U.S. Their deaths led to a fresh volley of accusations between the
governments of Cuba and the United States, each blaming the other
for policies they say encourage Cubans like the Bueno brothers to
risk their lives in the treacherous journey across the Florida
Straits. (Mike Williams/Cox News Service)
