   (NYT31) UNDATED -- Sept. 14, 2000 -- HOME-IMPROVEMENT -- Before
the introduction of modern latex and acrylic-based paints,
oil-based paint was the most common type of paint used for
commercial and residential applications. There was also another
type of paint that was made and used around the home, although
today few people have even heard of it. This was milk paint, and it
was made, as the name implies, with a milk base. (Ed Lipinski/The
