more careers than the typical family of four. He's been a farmer,
congressman, Washington economist, author, investment banker,
financial dealmaker. And in May, he added yet another line to the
book-length resume: Partner in Heartland Industrial Partners, a new
buyout firm with a game plan of buying small old-economy companies,
aggregating them into megaliths, and taking them public again.
Stockman with his wife Jennifer at their Greenwich home last week.
