<P>
   (NYT20) BOSTON -- Sept. 14, 2000 -- HOME-CYBER-CLUTTER-BOS --
The wires from computer monitors, keyboards, speakers, printers,
faxes, scanners, and phones are, for some, a visual nightmare. Some
label it cyber clutter. According to a recent Microsoft survey, the
furniture, interior-design, and industrial-design industries are
tackling wire management and techno-clutter problems. Using large
cup hooks, duct tape, nylon ties and Velcro are all inexpensive
ways to bind groups of wires together. (Pam Berry/The Boston Globe)
