   (NYT5) KOSOVSKA MITROVICA, Yugoslavia -- Sept. 14, 2000 --
YUGOSLAVIA-ELECTIONS -- Slobodan Milosevic's supporters broke up
the Kosovo campaign rally of Vojislav Kostunica, his strongest
challenger, Thursday, pelting the presidential candidate with waves
of rotten tomatoes and striking him in the face with a stone.
Bodyguards shield Kostunica, second from right, as eggs are thrown.
(Andrew Testa/The New York Times) LITE
