<P>
   (NYT1) SYDNEY, Australia -- Sept. 14, 2000 -- OLY-FLAME --
Jessie Niley-Dyer of the North Bondi surf rescue crew carries the
Olympic torch as other members of the surf rescue team paddle their
boat onto the shore at Bondi Beach in Sydney, Thursday. A million
people turned central Sydney into a giant street party on Thursday
to celebrate the arrival of the flame that heralds the opening of
the biggest Olympic Games in history. (Barton Silverman/The New
