MEHTA-MUSIC -- Zarin Mehta took over as the New York Philharmonic's
executive director just after Labor Day, replacing Deborah Borda,
who departed last December for a similar position with the Los
Angeles Philharmonic. At 61, he is considered a star in the small
world of classical-music management. Even before arriving in New
York to assume his new position, Mehta took a hand in the search
for a new music director to replace conductor Kurt Masur in 2002.
Mehta with sculpture of composer Gustav Mahler in his office in New
York. (Suzanne DeChillo/The New York Times)
