Fall-blooming anemones are little-known garden treasures of the
season that are ripe for discovery by a broader audience. There are
70 species of anemones. Their appearance suggests the delicacy of
spring flowers in both form and color. Anemones growing in a garden
in Milton, Mass. (Pam Berry/The Boston Globe)
